---
import Layout from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Frequently Asked Questions"
	description="Common questions about Conduital — pricing, data privacy, AI features, system requirements, and more."
>
	<div class="faq-list">
		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>Is this a subscription?</h2>
			<p>
				No. Conduital is a one-time purchase. You buy it, you own it. No
				recurring fees, no "your trial is expiring" emails. Future updates
				within your major version are included.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>Is my data stored in the cloud?</h2>
			<p>
				No. Conduital is local-first. Your projects, tasks, and notes live
				as markdown files on your computer. You can sync them however you
				like — Dropbox, iCloud, Git — but Conduital never uploads your data
				to our servers.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>How does the AI work?</h2>
			<p>
				Conduital connects to OpenAI-compatible APIs using your own API key.
				The AI features help you break through blocks, generate next actions,
				and make decisions — but they're entirely optional. The core
				productivity system works fully offline without any AI connection.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>Is there a free version?</h2>
			<p>
				Yes. The free tier includes the core dashboard, inbox, and project
				management features. Paid tiers unlock GTD workflows, advanced AI
				assistance, and the full Horizons of Focus system.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>What are the system requirements?</h2>
			<p>
				Windows 10 or later. No internet connection required for core features.
				AI features need a network connection and an OpenAI-compatible API key.
				A Mac version is planned for Q3 2026.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>Can I use my own AI provider?</h2>
			<p>
				Yes. Conduital works with any OpenAI-compatible API — including
				local models via Ollama or LM Studio. You're not locked into any
				single provider.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>What happens to my data if I stop using Conduital?</h2>
			<p>
				Nothing changes. Your data is standard markdown files that you own.
				Open them in any text editor, Obsidian, VS Code, or any other
				markdown-compatible tool. There's no proprietary format and no
				export step needed.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq-item">
			<h2>What if I need help?</h2>
			<p>
				Email <a href="mailto:greg@conduital.com">greg@conduital.com</a>.
				You'll hear back from a human, not a bot.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<p style="margin-top:3rem;text-align:center">
		<a
			href="https://conduital.gumroad.com/l/conduital"
			class="faq-cta"
		>
			Get Conduital →
		</a>
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	.faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}
	.faq-item {
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.5);
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
	.faq-item:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}
	.faq-item h2 {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.faq-item p {
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.faq-item a {
		color: var(--brand-primary, #2563eb);
	}
	.faq-cta {
		display: inline-block;
		background: #f59e0b;
		color: #1e3a5f;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		padding: 0.9rem 2.2rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		text-decoration: none;
	}
	.faq-cta:hover {
		background: #d97706;
	}
</style>
